Build a program
Usage: hop build [-o output] [options] [<package>]
       hop build [-o output] [options] <source-file> ...
Options:
    -o, --output <file>        Write output here (`-` for stdout)
    --platform <platform>      Target platform
    --arch <name>              Target architecture
    --output-format <format>   Output format (one of: executable, c, mir, tokens, ast)
    --cache-dir <dir>          Use this cache directory instead of the default
    --diag-format <fmt>        Diagnostics output format (one of: text, jsonl)
    -h, --help                 Show help and exit
<package>
    If no package or <source-file> is specified, the current directory is
    assumed to contain the package to build.
<platform>
    One of: cli-libc (default), cli-eval, wasm-min, playbit
<format>
    executable builds a usable program and is the default.
